
[1]arillus

   ARIL'LUS, n. The exterior coat or covering of a seed, fixed to it at
   the base only, investing it wholly or partially, and falling off
   spontaneously; by some writers called, from the Greek, Calyptra. It is
   either succulent, or cartilaginous; colored, elastic, rough or knotted.
